efense</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"color:#3498db;\">How Bombay Engineering Syndicate Supports You</span></strong></p>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Technical Matching:</strong> We help map your gas group, temp class, and protection needs</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Certification Support:</strong> ATEX, DGMS, CMRI documentation provided</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Custom Options:</strong> Top-terminal boxes, IP66 enclosures, VFD-ready builds</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Expertise:</strong> Decades of experience in hazardous zone equipment supply</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"color:#3498db;\">Typical Use Case</span></strong></p>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Scenario:</strong> Zone 1 ethylene unit (Gas Group IIB) requires 30 kW motors, T4 rating.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Solution:</strong> CG Ex d 160L frame flameproof motor, 415V, IP55, Class F, IIB + T4 certified, BASEEFA-approved.</p>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"color:#3498db;\">Final Thoughts</span></strong></p>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<p>Proper motor selection for hazardous zones is critical. Bombay Engineering Syndicate ensures you receive certified, compliant, and fit-for-purpose motors from CG PowerΓÇösupported by accurate specifications and documentation.</p>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.bombayengg.net/contact/\">Contact us today</a> to evaluate your hazardous area project and get expert recommendations.</p>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<p style=\"font-style: italic;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">By: Manish Chandrani; +919825014977</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n','Hazardous-Area Motors: A Deep Dive into Gas Groups IIA & IIB','hazardous-area-motors-a-deep-dive-into-gas-groups-iia-iib',NULL,NULL,'A technical guide on motors for hazardous areas (Gas IIA/IIB), covering Ex d, Ex e, and Ex nA types, temperature classes, certifications, and CG Power solutions. Bombay Engg ensures fast, compliant motor supply for Zone 1/2 applications.','2025-07-26 00:00:00',1),(4,'ie34.png',NULL,'<div class=\"container\">\r\n<p>Motor efficiency standards help industries adopt energy-efficient equipment while meeting global environmental regulations. The International Electrotechnical Commission (IEC) developed the IE classification system to standardize electric motor efficiency levels globally.</p>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"color:#3498db;\">1. What Is an IE Efficiency Class?</span></strong></p>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<p>IE stands for \"International Efficiency.\" The classes are defined by <strong>IEC 60034-30-1</strong>, which categorizes electric motors based on their energy efficiency. Higher IE class = greater efficiency and energy savings.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>IE1 ΓÇô Standard Efficiency</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>IE2 ΓÇô High Efficiency</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>IE3 ΓÇô Premium Efficiency</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>IE4 ΓÇô Super Premium Efficiency</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"color:#3498db;\">2. Efficiency Comparison Table (Indicative %)</span></strong></p>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"8\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%;\">\r\n	<thead style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff;\">\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th>Power (kW)</th>\r\n			<th>IE1</th>\r\n			<th>IE2</th>\r\n			<th>IE3</th>\r\n			<th>IE4</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>1.1</td>\r\n			<td>77.4%</td>\r\n			<td>81.4%</td>\r\n			<td>84.1%</td>\r\n			<td>86.1%</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>7.5</td>\r\n			<td>88.6%</td>\r\n			<td>90.6%</td>\r\n			<td>92.6%</td>\r\n			<td>94.1%</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>15</td>\r\n			<td>90.6%</td>\r\n			<td>92.6%</td>\r\n			<td>93.9%</td>\r\n			<td>95.4%</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>30</td>\r\n			<td>91.7%</td>\r\n			<td>93.6%</td>\r\n			<td>95.0%</td>\r\n			<td>96.3%</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 13px;\">*Values are indicative and vary slightly with pole number and voltage.</p>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"color:#3498db;\">3. Global Regulatory Mandates</span></strong></p>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>India:</strong> BIS mandates IE2 minimum for new motors since 2018; IE3 becoming common in OEM specs</li>\r\n	<li><strong>EU:</strong> IE3 is the minimum standard since 2021</li>\r\n	<li><strong>USA (NEMA):</strong> Equivalent to IE3 under EPAct/EISA regulations</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"color:#3498db;\">4. Long-Term Cost Savings</span></strong></p>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<p>Even a 2ΓÇô3% gain in motor efficiency significantly reduces energy bills over the motorΓÇÖs lifespan. Consider the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A motor\'s purchase price is typically just 2ΓÇô5% of its lifetime cost</li>\r\n	<li>Electricity represents ~95% of total cost of ownership</li>\r\n	<li>IE3 or IE4 motors may pay back the price difference in 6ΓÇô18 months via energy savings</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"color:#3498db;\">5. Where Do IE3/IE4 Motors Matter Most?</span></strong></p>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Continuous-duty applications (pumps, compressors, fans)</li>\r\n	<li>Remote or difficult-to-maintain installations</li>\r\n	<li>Industries with high energy usage: pharma, chemicals, textiles, cement, steel</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"color:#3498db;\">6. CG Power Motors & Bombay Engineering Syndicate</span></strong></p>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<p>CG Power offers a comprehensive range of <strong>IE2, IE3, and IE4-compliant motors</strong>, both standard and flameproof. These motors are available in:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Frame sizes: 63 to 355</li>\r\n	<li>Power range: 0.37 kW to 355 kW</li>\r\n	<li>Construction: Cast iron or aluminum</li>\r\n	<li>Certifications: BIS, BEE Star Rating, ATEX, CMRI (for flameproof variants)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"color:#3498db;\">7. Bombay Engineering Syndicate helps industries transition to energy-efficient systems by:</span></strong><