┬á\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"color:#3498db;\">2. Bearing Selection Factors</span></strong></p>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Load Type:</strong> Radial vs. axial vs. combined load requirements.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Motor Size & Speed:</strong> High-speed motors often require precision ball bearings; large motors may need roller or sleeve bearings.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Application:</strong> Pumps, compressors, and fans each have unique bearing demands.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>VFD Applications:</strong> Bearings may need insulation or hybrid ceramic designs to prevent stray current damage.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"color:#3498db;\">3. Common Bearing Failures</span></strong></p>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Lubrication Failure:</strong> Insufficient or contaminated grease leads to overheating and wear.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Misalignment:</strong> Shaft misalignment causes uneven loading and early failure.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Electrical Damage:</strong> Stray currents from VFDs can cause pitting in races (fluting).</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Contamination:</strong> Dust, moisture, or chemicals reduce bearing life significantly.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"color:#3498db;\">4. Maintenance Best Practices</span></strong></p>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Follow lubrication schedules using correct grade of grease or oil.</li>\r\n	<li>Ensure alignment checks during installation and servicing.</li>\r\n	<li>Use insulated or hybrid bearings for VFD-driven motors.</li>\r\n	<li>Store bearings in dry, clean environments to avoid contamination before installation.</li>\r\n	<li>Regularly monitor temperature and vibration to predict bearing health.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"color:#3498db;\">CG Power Bearing Practices</span></strong></p>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<p>CG Power motors are designed with high-quality bearings from reputed manufacturers (SKF, FAG, NTN) and optimized for Indian operating conditions. Options for insulated bearings, sleeve bearings, and customized bearing solutions are available for demanding applications.</p>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"color:#3498db;\">Final Thoughts</span></strong></p>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<p>Bearings are vital to motor reliability. By choosing the right type and practicing proper maintenance, industries can extend motor life and reduce unplanned downtime. Bombay Engineering Syndicate ensures that every CG Power motor supplied is equipped with suitable bearings for its intended application and provides guidance on their upkeep.</p>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.bombayengg.net/contact/\">Contact us today</a> for expert advice on motor bearing selection and maintenance.</p>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<p style=\"font-style: italic;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">By: Manish Chandrani; +919825014977</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n','Bearing Types in Electric Motors ΓÇô Selection & Maintenance','bearing-types-in-electric-motors-selection-maintenance-1',NULL,NULL,'An in-depth guide to bearings in electric motorsΓÇöcovering ball, roller, angular contact, and sleeve types, along with selection factors, common failures, and maintenance tips. Highlights how CG Power motors use premium bearings, with support from Bombay','2025-09-16 00:00:00',1),(12,'ie4.jpg',NULL,'<div class=\"container\">\r\n<p>Energy efficiency has become a key priority across industries. With electricity costs rising and sustainability goals tightening, upgrading from IE1 or IE2 motors to IE3 or IE4 can result in substantial long-term savings. CG Power offers a full range of high-efficiency motors designed to deliver superior performance while reducing operational costs.</p>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"color:#3498db;\">1. What Are IE Efficiency Classes?</span></strong></p>\r\n┬á\r\n\r\n<p>The International Electrotechnical Commission (IEC 60034-30) defines efficiency standards for motors. These are classified as:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>IE1:</strong> Standard Efficiency